  "description": [
    "er Vol 62 No 43 26 October 1962 Games Slated At Dance Set For Halloween Personnel attending the bg All Hands Halloween Dance slat ed for next Tuesday night at the Recreation enter Bldg 114 will have ample opportunity to try their skill at ducking for apple and other games in keeping with the seasonal spirit Prizes will be awarded to the most skillful The big dance slated for a 2000 blastoff will feature music by the Naval Station Red Devils as conducted by MUC bred Hutchins In order that every one may reach home safely before carriages turn into pumpkins a 2330 closing will be in effect Noisemakers candy and hats all free will be offered those at tending As the old saying goes Variety is the spice of life so in addition to the above the Snack Bar will be open offering all types of goodies There will be no admission charge to this gala affair All Newportbased enlisted per sonnel their dependents and guests are invited to attend the big All Hands affair Foreign Officers Tour CruDesLant Supply Spaces A visit to CruiserDestroyer Force headquarters and units last Thursday and Friday highlighted the Naval Supply Management Course"
  ],
